</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dhFVuh gFqzWs pf-122_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fbKhWw bnrVBh pf-123_"><strong>Host a ‘Tea and Talk’ session</strong> - Gather friends, colleagues, or family members for an informal chat about mental health.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fbKhWw bnrVBh pf-125_"><strong>Use social media</strong> - Share your thoughts using #TimeToTalk to raise awareness and encourage dialogue.
